    <descriptionText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px">This is an Execute Next Steps question, but it is closed-ended and not directly linked to the previous conversation. Look at how it is phrased compared to the best question.<BR><BR>The best question is, "I understand the challenges that you’re facing in your practice.  How do you suggest that we discuss, with your entire staff, both the challenges and the ways that we can help you with them?"<BR><BR>This Execute Next Steps question makes a clear advance, while framing the question in a way that demonstrates your understanding of the practice’s key business issues.<BR><BR><B>Here’s how Dr. Hayes would have answered that question:</B><BR><BR>"Let’s plan an in-service program for the staff to educate them on your product and programs.  You can set up that appointment with the front office staff.  Thanks."</welcomeText>]]></descriptionText>
